OL,1,D]S737{kkkc5FNext warns of higher prices
OL,2,D]S555{jjj25Fas costs rise              
OL,3,D]Suuu{rrzq5F                           
OL,4,T#######################################
OL,5, Next has said it will raise its prices 
OL,6, this year to offset increased wages as 
OL,7, well as higher shipping costs.         
OL,9,FIt said prices for its spring and      
OL,10,Fsummer clothing and homeware ranges    
OL,11,Fwould rise by 3.7% from a year earlier,
OL,12,Fwhile it expects a 6% increase for     
OL,13,Fautumn and winter goods.               
OL,15,FIts forecast came as it said sales for 
OL,16,Fthe three months to 25 December were up
OL,17,F20% compared with pre-pandemic 2019.   
OL,19,FNext also upped its profit forecast for
OL,20,Fthe year.                              
